other_tests.findings: Pathological examination indicated a small-cell carcinoma that was consistent with Merkel-cell carcinoma.
Revealed malignant cells that were consistent with Merkel-cell carcinoma.
Final tissue margin was free of tumor.
Showed drainage to lymph nodes in both sides of the neck.
Specimen showed foci of malignant cells within the liver parenchyma, with positive staining for cytokeratin 20, chromogranin, and neuron-specific enolase.
